description:
The software shall store the following information about Documents:

  • Document Unique System ID (i.e. 1, 2, etc.)
  • Document Type Code (i.e. SRD, HRD, PSAC, etc.)
  • Revision
  • Associated Peer Review
  • Review Status
    PASS
    FAIL
    Not Started
  • In-Work
  • Closed
  • Associated Files -why do we need this when we have the latest released and draft?
  • Latest Released Revision
  • Latest Draft Revision

The software shall support the following Document types for a DO-178 project type:

  • PSAC:    Plan for Software Aspects of Certification
  • SCMP:    Software Configuration Management Plan
  • SRS:      Software Requirements Standards
  • SDP:      Software Development Plan
  • SQAP:    Software Quality Assurance Plan
  • SCS:      Software Code Standards
  • SDS:      Software Design Standards
  • MBDS:   Model-Based Design Standards
  • SVP:      Software Verification Plan
  • SRD:      System Requirements Document
  • SDD:      System Design Document
  • SWRD:   Software Requirements Document
  • SWDD:   Software Design Document
  • SCI:       Software Configuration Index
  • SECI:     Software Environment Lifecycle Index
  • SWVCP:  Software Verification Cases and Procedures
  • SVR:      Software Verification Results
  • SAS:      Software Accomplishment Summary
  • TQP:      Tool Qualification Plan
  • TQR:      Tool Qualification Results
  • PDI:       Parameter Data Items
  • RTM:      Requirements Traceability Matrix

The software shall support the following Document types for a DO-278 project type:

  • TBD
The software shall support baselining of documents such that any additional changes to the document will trigger an automatic increment in the version number.
The software shall provide a view of the documents in a directory file format similar to QCMS:

The software shall support the following Document types for a DO-178 project type:

  • Peer Review
    Planning
    Requirements
    Conceptual Design
    Code
    Integration
    Test Procedures
    Test Results
    Accomplishment Summary
  • Transition Review
    Planning
    Requirements
    Preliminary Design
    Critical Design
    Code
    Integration
    Verification
    Conformity
  • Compliance
    Planning
    Development
    Verification
    Final

The software shall support the following Review styles for a DO-278 project type:

  • TBD

The software shall support the following Review styles for a DO-254 project type:

  • TBD

The software shall store the following information about Review Types:

  • Review Unique System ID (i.e. 1, 2, etc.)
  • Review Title (i.e. Requirements Peer Review, etc.)
  • Review Description (i.e. CCB 001 Req. Review)
  • Review Type (i.e. Transition, Peer)
  • Review Date
  • Review Revision
  • Associated Checklist
  • Review Status (Not Started, In-Work, PASS, FAIL)
  • Associated Files
  • Action Items?
The software shall provide an interface to create sign-in sheets for Review members.
The software shall support the concept of Baselining, such that any subsequent changes to reviews automatically increments the version number.

The software shall tailor the Review types according to what is required by the DO-178() DAL and permit the use of optional Review types if desired by the user.

Design Note: Lockdown required aspects to ensure they don't remove needed checklist review items for compliance. Changes to templates would primarily be additions, not deletions to ensure compliance.

The software shall tailor the Review types according to what is required by the selected DO-178() supplements.

Design Note: Lockdown required aspects to ensure they don't remove needed checklist review items for compliance. Changes to templates would primarily be additions, not deletions to ensure compliance.

The software shall support the following types of requirements:

  • System Requirements
  • High Level Requirements

The software shall support the following fields for a System Requirement:

  • Requirement ID
  • Requirement Description
  • Requirement Source
  • Safety-Related
  • Implementation

The software shall support parsing an uploaded CSV, XLS or XLSX file to import System Requirements, with the following format:
Requirement ID, Requirement Description, Requirement Source, Safety-Related, Implementation

The software shall support the following fields for all Levels of Requirements:

  • Requirement Description
  • Category
  • Verification Method
  • Associated System Requirements
  • Is the requirement Derived?
  • Requirement ID
  • Justification (required for derived requirements)
  • User-defined Attribute field (string)
    Attributes shall be selected through a multi-select drop-down menu with another field that permits the entry of a string incorporating current attributes robustness, derived and safety.

The software shall support parsing an uploaded CSV, XLS or XLSX file to import High-Level Requirements, with the following format:
Requirement ID, Requirement Description, Category, Verification Method, Associated System Requirements, Derived Flag, Justification.

The software shall support the following fields for all Requirements:

  • Requirement ID
  • Requirement Description
  • Associated High-Level Requirements
  • Is the requirement Derived?
  • Attributes shall be selected through a multi Select drop-down menu with an additional Other attribute and a text field for other.
  • Justification (required for derived requirements)

The software shall support parsing an uploaded CSV, XLS or XLSX file to import Low-Level Requirements, with the following format:

Requirement ID, Requirement Description, Associated High-Level Requirements, Derived Flag, Justification
The software shall support the automatic numbering of requirements.
The software shall mark requirements as deleted if requested and will not reuse previously used numbering of requirements.
The software shall support attaching and displaying one image with a requirement.
The software shall support the concept of Baselining, such that any subsequent changes to System Requirements automatically increments the version number.
The software shall support the concept of Baselining, such that any subsequent changes to High-Level Requirements automatically increments the version number.
The software shall support the concept of Baselining, such that any subsequent changes to Low Level Requirements automatically increments the version number.
The software shall support the concept of Baselining, such that any subsequent changes to test cases automatically increments the version number.
The software shall require that a justification be provided for all derived software requirements.
The software shall support requirements, test case, and code tag tracing.
The software shall support bi-directional tracing between High-Level Requirements and Low-Level Requirements.
The software shall support bi-directional tracing between Low-Level Requirements and Source Code.
The software shall support bi-directional tracing between Low-Level Requirements and Source Code.
The software shall support bi-directional tracing between Low-Level Requirements and Test Cases.
The software shall output selectable bi-directional tracing as a downloadable file.
The software shall support bi-directional tracing between high-Level Requirements and Source Code if there are no low-level requirements.

The software shall store the following information about Problem Reports:
  • ID
  • Title
  • Criticality
  • Safety Related?
  • Status
  • Assigned To
  • Opened By
  • Date Opened
  • Date Modified
  • Close Date
  • Associated Files
  • History
  • Description of Change
  • Severity Type

The software shall store the following information about Problem Report History:
  • Status
  • Modified by User
  • Date of Modification
  • Description of Modification Action?
  • Severity Type
Create a problem report flow and add to PACT. The point of this is to see have the transitions flow and define the states.

The software shall only permit users with QA and CM roles on a project to delete PRs.

(SJG: maybe allow the user to mark requirement to be deleted with some mechanism i.e. strikethrough, color change, attribute)
The software shall display only those PRs associated with the selected project.
The software shall support an option to display only those PRs associated with the current user for the selected project.
The software shall generate a report of Open PRs suspected of having real impact on System/Item function, along with what other requirements may be affected.
The software shall provide an interface to scan for files in a GitHub Repository and generate Source code items.
The software shall provide a method to associate source code items with low-level requirements.
The software shall provide a method track the association between low level requirements and source code items, including source code items that are not associated with any low-level requirement
The software shall provide a method to associate source code items with high-level requirements.

The software shall store the following information about Document Comments:
  • Comment Unique ID
  • Document Revision
  • Date of Comment Last Modified
  • Status
  • Requested By
  • Assigned To
  • Comment Description(s)

The software shall store the following information about Action Items:
  • ID
  • Status
  • Date
  • Item Description
  • Assigned To
  • Opened By
The software shall have the option to email the assigned person when an action item is created or changed.
The software shall provide a mechanism to import user-defined checklist templates.

The software shall provide a mechanism to override the default checklist templates with a set of user-defined templates on a project.

Design Note: The override will happen automatically. If no user-defined template exists, the default template will be used, otherwise, the user-defined template will be enabled.

The software shall provide an interface to make global modifications to checklist templates in the following fields:

  • Company Name
  • Logo
The system shall provide a way to export checklists in a CSV format.
The software shall provide a mechanism to import user-defined checklist templates.

The software shall tailor the checklist templates according to what is required by the DO-178() DAL.

Design Note: Lock down required aspects to ensure they don't remove needed checklist review items for compliance. Changes to templates would primarily be additions, not deletions to ensure compliance.

The software shall tailor the Review types according to what is required by the selected DO-178() supplements.

Design Note: Lockdown required aspects to ensure they don't remove needed checklist review items for compliance. Changes to templates would primarily be additions, not deletions to ensure compliance.
The software shall provide pre-loaded default checklist templates for all supported Document and Review types.

The software shall store the following information about Checklists:
  • ID
  • Association (Document, Review)
  • ID of Associated Item
  • Evaluator
  • Evaluation Date
  • Checklist Items

The software shall store the following information about Checklist Items:
  • Item Number
  • Checklist Item Description
  • Reference
  • Applicable DAL
  • State (PASS, FAIL, N/A)
  • Notes
  • Supplements

The software shall require a Justification be given in the Notes field for any checklist question whose state is N/A.

Design Note: Preface the justification with the text "Justification:" to make clear which note text pertains to the N/A.

The software shall require a Defect Comment: be given in the Notes field for any checklist question whose state is FAIL.

Design Note: Preface the defect comment with the text "Defect Comment:" to make clear which note text pertains to the FAIL.
The software shall require all users to login before accessing any other portions of the software.

The software shall have the following roles for users:
  • Administrator
  • Program Manager
  • Configuration Manager
  • Quality Assurance
  • Team Member
  • View-Only User
  • Restricted View
The software shall have configurable per-project access for each user. Each user can be configured to have access to one or more projects, or all projects.
The software shall allow only Administrators to change any other users settings.
The software shall allow users to inherit more than one role.
The software shall only allow Administrators to change an Administrators user settings.

The software shall store the following information about users:
  • Username
  • Password
  • First Name
  • Last Name
  • Company Affiliation
  • Email Address
  • Roles
  • Project Access
  • User is Enabled
  • Users password needs to be reset

The software shall allow Administrator's to perform the following actions for a user on a global or per-project basis:

  • Add
  • Modify
  • Delete

The software shall store the following information about Projects:
  • Project Identifier
  • Name
  • Type of Project
  • Access Level (Public, Protected Private)
  • Permitted Users (for protected access)
  • Assurance Level (if applicable)

The software shall associate all lifecycle data with a specific Project Identifier and Type of Project.

Design Note: Common artifacts should be shared so they do not need to be duplicated.

Needs Clarification

The software shall support different types of projects within a specific Project Identifier.

Needs Clarification
The software shall provide an interface where the user may filter the data they wish to view based upon selections made against the fields stored in HLR-013000
The software shall permit limiting the visibility of a project to only specific individuals.

The data for each client (organization) shall be viewable and modifiable only by that organization or authorized Patmos employees. No organizations users will be able to see another organizations data.

At no time shall any user in the system be able to access data from another clients database. Once a user has been authenticated, the user will be connected to the database for their organization. With the exception of changes to the users credentials, all further data access will occur within the users organizations database.
The software shall provide versioning for all life cycle data.

The software shall support the import and export of files in the OMG ReqIF 1.2 Format. Importing and exporting any relevant items into and out of PACT including but not limited to Documents, System Requirements High-Level Requirements, Low-level Requirements, Check Lists, Test Cases, Reviews, Problem, Reports and any relevant linkages between them.
The software shall implement all features of ReqIF# (https://www.reqifsharp.org/) in Ruby 2.5.
The software shall successfully import a file exported in ReqIF format from IBM Doors without errors.
The software shall successfully export a file from PACT in ReqIF format and successfully import it into IBM Doors without errors.

The software shall generate a requirements trace matrix. The format is as follows:
See Steve's example
The software shall generate a requirements trace matrix that allows the user to select which linkages that they see.
The software shall enable the user to select from the standard temples when creating a new project for each of the data items.
The software shall give the user the ability to select which templates to use from a particular directory.
The template shall be modifiable by the user.
